Montenegro Backs 9.6 Million-Euro Loans for National Airline

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-04-07T16:32:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/montenegro-backs-9-6-million-euro-loans-for-national-airline.html
Montenegro’s government said it
would guarantee 9.6 million euros ($13.7 million) in loans for
state-run Montenegro Airlines to help its flag carrier add
routes, buy new aircraft and maintain its fleet.  The carrier, whose current fleet includes five Fokker 100’s
and three Embraer 195’s, plans to spend 4 million euros to buy
another Embraer 195, while one million euros would go toward
repairing its existing aircraft, the  Finance Ministry  said in
an e-mailed statement.  Another 4.6 million euros will be used to fund the addition
new destinations to airline’s existing 20 routes.  Montenegro Airlines has already made arrangements for a 2
million-euro loan from Hipotekarna banka AD in Podgorica and for
2.4 million euros from NLB Montenegrobanka, a unit of Slovenian
Nova Ljubljanska Banka d.d.. It used government guarantees
approved today for the credits as well.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
